page.title: 06PLANTS AND TREES
page.content: There are not many unusual or rare plants in this area.{90%}of people said that they had not seen any rare or unusual plants but{1.1% }said they had seen Mulberry,{1.1%}Teasle and {1.1%}Hymalayan Balsalm. The most popular trees seen in this area are Oak{22%}, Horse Chestnut with{19%}and Sycamore{12%}. The others are Sweet Chestnut, Beech, Ash, Birch, Pines, Hawthorn, Fir Trees, Maple, Yew, Cedar and Elder. This shows that there are quite a few trees in this area. In our school field there are a lot of Sycamores and nettle bushes. At the top end though there are some planted trees which are not wild as they are in the grounds of a large Victorian house. A few streets in this area are tree lined and a lot of old gardens have probably got a tree in them because we have a lot of old houses.
